Business Briefs
Norton Healthcare Ltd., a subsidiary of Ivax Corp.,
received approval from the British Department of Health to
sell metered dose inhaler versions of an agent used to manage
bronchial asthma.
   ---
   Mobil Telecommunications Technologies Corp. said its
partner, Secter Sdn. Bhd., received a license from the
Malaysian government to develop a nationwide and
international messaging system.
   ---
   Rohr Inc., an aircraft parts maker, plans to build a $25
million manufacturing facility in Clark County, Ark.
   ---
   McCormick U.K. PLC, a unit of McCormick  Co., said it
acquired Glentham International, Northampton, England, from
Harrisons and Crosfield PLC.